lead_paragraph: Quarterbacks went one-two at Thursday's NFL Draft as the Los Angeles Rams took Jared Goff with the first pick, and the Philadelphia Eagles followed suit by naming signal caller Carson Wentz with the second choice.

headline.print_headline: Rams Take Quarterback Goff With First Pick of Draft
